The '''Salliche Agricultural Corporation''', or '''Salliche Ag''', was an agricultural company headquartered on [[Salliche/Legends|Salliche]], an [[Agriworld/Legends|agriworld]] also home to the [[Vaults of Narner]].

[[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] was its primary customer, due to the proximity of many of its agriworlds to the [[Capital/Legends|capital]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. However, it likely had other customers in the Inner Core due to the high population density of the region, especially along the first part of the [[Corellian Run/Legends|Corellian Run]].

==History==
Sometime before the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], it sued [[Dasobo Meats]], claiming that Dasobo stole their genetic secrets used to breed [[Gornt/Legends|gornts]].

It was run by [[House Harbright]], and the company had operations on many [[Planet/Legends|planets]] it held, from [[Broest/Legends|Broest]] and [[Ruan]] to [[Yulant]]. [[Leah Nynel]] was the company's spokesman in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], the same year the Clone Wars started.

Salliche Ag used droids to replace workers who rebelled against the company after the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], but returned to organic workers in response to the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] invasion. The company welcomed refugees to Salliche Ag planets ostensibly to be sheltered and work there, but in reality, the company was setting itself up for favorable treatment under the expected Yuuzhan Vong victory and control of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. After the droids revolted and protested their treatment, Salliche Ag ceased accepting refugees.

